##In the days of disorder, how can ordinary people in the affected areas live their normal lives?

❶

"The white coat came off,

But I still have my camera."

Photographer Wengi took this photo outside the hospital where he once worked. From the outside, the hospital was so quiet that no one knew what was going on inside. Wengi was wearing two layers of face masks, one made of cotton and the other of smog, which didn't do much to protect him. She gawked at the door of the hospital for a while, but didn't go in and drove back.

"All for the health of the people, " reads a large stone carved in the doorway of Central Theater Command General Hospital, a designated hospital for new-born pneumonia patients. When Wengi came to the door of the hospital, they were talking around some boxes. Wengi said, "I hope it's a mask. "
Six months ago, Wengi quit the hospital and joined a photography studio. After the outbreak, Wengi's father suddenly let go of his daughter's decision to give up her stable job at the hospital: "It's better to be in a new job, safe. " Before the city was shut down in Wuhan, Wengi thought the epidemic would pass in 10 days and a half months, i'm just glad I don't have to work long hours.
But as the outbreak spread, Wengi's mindset changed. After her resignation, she remained in the Department of the inspection department. In the first few days after the closure of the city, the group was filled with news of various material shortages. Express deliveries were suspended, and colleagues were unable to receive protective clothing purchased out of their own pocket. Wengi, however, "could do nothing to help. " She confided to her friend, "I really want to be on the line, I want to be with my former colleagues... "
For the past eight years, the intersection of Zhongnan Road and Wuluo Road, pictured below, has been her daily commute. In Memory, 7:00 a. m. one, the bus and the private car then will be this intersection jam-packed, not 20 minutes can not open. At 4 p.m. on Jan. 24, when she walked back down the road with her camera, only one red and one yellow were left in the bright colors of the delivery boys'uniforms.

It was the second day of the city's closure, and even the haze of the day put a huge mask on Wuhan to prevent the spread of the virus, but also suffocate the city's daily life. The Wuhan of "the thoroughfare of the nine provinces" has stalled. Bus and train stations were closed, and the scenic spot was empty. The highway crossing leaving Wuhan was closed. "Our city is sick, Wuhan is really sick, " Wengi said
On the road from Hanyang to Wuchang, a sign and road information were scrolled across an electronic screen that read, "exit route closed, please understand and support. ".
At 5 p.m. , Wengi returned home from the shoot, took a shower, and immediately began working on today's story: "My lab coat is off, but I still have my camera. "
In the middle of the revision, she saw the news from her former department. In the photo, her former colleagues, dressed in full protective gear, compared with the camera.
A few days before the closure of the city, Wengi did not know the situation of the epidemic, had advised the medical workers do not do "great man" , after the closure of the city, to see the former colleagues, but could not help lamenting their "great" .

❷
A sense of order in your life
After returning from the shoot, Wengi decided not to go out except to buy groceries. She turned the camera on her home life, day by day, and so it has continued.
Wengi basks in colorful socks on her balcony on Jan. 25.
On January 26, Wengi stockpiled a basket of beautiful oranges.

Wengi and his father live in a small home of only seventy square meters, decoration is also simple, Wengi prefer to shoot local. Wengi photographed the smiling trash can on Jan. 29.
A growing wood sorrel plant in a pot on Jan. 31.
Looking down from the balcony, the neighbor's yard opened a small rose, long out of the fence. "In such a season, " Wengi wrote, "life is still here, and flowers are still in bloom. " Photo taken on February 7.
In late January, Wengi began practicing calligraphy, she said, to get a long-lost "peace" while copying Buddhist Sutras, on Feb. 12.

The balcony is the only place to the outside world, February 18 is a rare sunny day, the wind blowing, the windmill on the balcony will turn.

On Feb. 10, Wengi returned with a bag of green, fresh vegetables, the leaves of which had been kindly removed by his boss. These days, twice-weekly shopping is her only outing, she always wears two masks, a thin film gloves, towards the community door of the vegetable peddler go straight, quick return. The stall is a Shandong couple, early in the morning to pull a cart of vegetables to sell at the gate of the residential area, the price is almost the same as usual.
Housewife Xiaojie's family photo diary was inspired by Wengi.

The first few days after the city was sealed off, Xiao Jie was anxious. Fengcheng came to the home as a guest of friends appeared pneumonia symptoms, waiting for the results of that period of time, Xiaojie "the whole person's heart has been hanging. ". Once the daughter came up to find her mother, Xiao Jie for a moment did not control, shouted at her daughter, "you find a place to play, I am not in the mood to accompany you! "
Even if later know, what the friend gets is the ordinary pneumonia, Xiao Jie always difficult to dispel in the heart nervous feeling. In late January, bad news was all over the Internet, and she was on the phone with friends, talking about the epidemic until the wee hours of the morning.
It wasn't until she saw a few of Wengi's family photos that she was able to ease off a little. Looking at the brightly colored pictures, Xiaojie felt "like she was back to her normal life. " After that, she began to record the family's life in the same way.
A week before last, Xiaojie brought back a narcissus from her sister's flower shop. It was still in Bud when the city was sealed, and it was in full bloom on February 6. Fourteen days is just enough time, measured by the perception of daffodils, for one shy and defeated plant to wait for the next mounting army.

The youngest daughter Aiya birthday that day, because did not usher in an imaginary lively birthday, Aiya has been pouting mouth dissatisfaction, Xiaojie took her to observe the ecological bottle inside the small shrimp to divert attention.
It was the morning of January 23, the first day of the siege of Wuhan, and alas'fourth birthday. The children did not understand the meaning of "city closure" , let alone what "COVID-19" meant, they expect their friends to come along with their grandparents and grandparents to celebrate her birthday, sing happy songs, blow out candles and cut cake. After all, "all the other kids have them. "
After passing the bedroom, Xiao Jie saw the brothers and sisters glued to the window glass and looked down. Drinking milk, they said, "Will Mengmeng and Shanshan Come? They said they would. " Xiao Jie has a sour nose.

Xiao Jie held the two children in her arms and explained patiently, "we are fighting a war now. The enemy's name is coronavirus. It will make you sick. Now there are many, many people out there who have been hurt by it. Doctors and nurses at the front are helping the sick. The men behind us must stay at home, where the enemy will not find us. "
The cakes ordered the day before the siege arrived on time. In the evening, the family of four gave the little girl a simple birthday.
On January 29, Xiao Jie shared with her friends an updated recipe for the foulest instant noodles known as Foshan Mushroom stewed chicken noodles: Pour pure water in the Pan, wait for a small bubble to appear on the wall, then pour in the bread and all the condiments, boil the water for another two minutes, turn off the heat, sprinkle some black pepper, drop a few drops of sesame oil. Now, a modified version of the mushroom chicken noodle stew has become a family favorite.

A few days before the Lantern Festival, Xiao Jie and her husband made several kinds of rice wine dumplings for their children. There are sesame fillings, peanut fillings, different colors. As usual, the cat got up early in the morning and waited for her "father" in the kitchen. As soon as "father" arrived, the cat jumped onto his shoulder.

On Feb. 7, Xiaojie and her children began making noodles, "cat ears, " a family tradition. Under her direction, the children rolled the dough into small balls, dusted them with flour, and pressed them forward with their thumbs. The daughter also practiced both hands to press the "stunt" , "mother you see, I can also close my eyes to press
Before the outbreak, children often help Xiaojie peel beans, choose dishes, beat eggs, dumplings. Watching the two children focus on making cat ears, Xiaojie found that the scene is no different from the usual picture of a family cooking, she felt unprecedented relaxation and enjoyment.

❸
"when the nine days of September are spent and the cold is gone,
Is when the wind blows in."
Though unable to go to the front, Wengi has been involved in volunteer online material coordination since the beginning of the new year, adding four or five groups of 500 people, frequently posting material donation cases and volunteer recruitment messages in her circle of friends. With the help of volunteers, dozens of tons of disinfectant and thousands of tons of free vegetables were sent to hospitals and communities in the affected areas. A month on, these jobs have become part of life in Wengi.
Wengi was part of a group of civilian volunteers called Eqi support, which has helped with several donations, received from some hospitals and communities where the donations were received.
Wengi's fellow photographer, Luna, also volunteers online at her home. In late January, Luna helped friends outside the country to contact the channels for material donations, which were difficult to transport, coupled with the exposure of Red Cross material deployment around January 30, and the frequency of bad news, Luna was in low spirits.
One day in early February, Luna, who had been staying at home for days in Xianning, Hubei Province, noticed a plum blossom in her backyard. Plum blossom is the city flower of Wuhan, she went to the yard broke a branch, inserted in the vase at home, recorded this wipe the precious bright winter. "Every Dark Day remembers where the light comes from, " she wrote on her Weibo Account.

For a week, she switched clubs. In the days when she could only look at a plum tree, some warm-hearted people and things became her "source of light" —— she had a friend who lived overseas, and her father contracted Lotus roots in the local Lotus pond, "The money that contracts pond still borrows with his daughter. " But did not think these Lotus harvest just hit epidemic situation, old gentleman donated whole car lotus root to epidemic area.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The ancients have made "nine nine cold map, " the habit of greeting spring, from the winter solstice into nine daily trace a petal, "to be nine nine cold, is the spring wind into the house. In the days that followed, the plum blossoms began to bloom.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
